Crowds cheered for the those in the lead packs and the also-rans on the warm, sunny autumn day. Grete Waitz of Norway won the women's division for a record ninth time in 2:28:07. The winner in the field of 23478 _ largest ever for a marathon _ was Steve Jones of Wales, who finished in 2 hours, 8 minutes and 20 seconds, only seven seconds off the course record. Television watchers of the 19th annual New York City Marathon followed the step-by-step progress Sunday of the leaders, but many spectators on the course scanned the thousands of runners for a familar face. 